# 📡 FPGA-Based Smart Relay Health Monitoring System

![FPGA](https://img.shields.io/badge/FPGA-Xilinx%20Spartan--6-red.svg)
![MCU](https://img.shields.io/badge/MCU-NodeMCU%20ESP8266-blue.svg)
![Protocol](https://img.shields.io/badge/protocol-MQTT%20%7C%20UART-green.svg)
![HDL](https://img.shields.io/badge/HDL-Verilog%20RTL-orange.svg)
![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-Completed-brightgreen.svg)

A real-time relay health monitoring and control system integrating **FPGA**, **embedded systems**, and **cloud communication**. The system continuously monitors temperature, relay operational status, and relay health condition — classifying it as `GOOD`, `WARNING`, or `BAD` — and transmits live data to the cloud over **MQTT**.

---

## 🧠 Overview

Built around the **Xilinx Spartan-6 FPGA** and **NodeMCU (ESP8266)**, this project reads analog temperature data from an **LM35** sensor, classifies the relay health on the NodeMCU, and sends the result to the FPGA over **UART**. The FPGA controls a **2-channel 5V relay module** using clock-synthesized switching logic written in **Verilog (RTL)**. All data is simultaneously published to the cloud via **MQTT** for remote monitoring and diagnostics.

---

## 🎯 Objective

To design a reliable and intelligent monitoring system that:

1. Detects early signs of relay failure
2. Monitors environmental temperature in real time
3. Classifies relay health condition — GOOD / WARNING / BAD
4. Provides live cloud updates via MQTT
5. Enables FPGA-based deterministic relay control using clock synthesis and push button input

