## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Xilinx ISE or Vivado
- Arduino IDE with ESP8266 board package
- MQTT broker (Mosquitto / HiveMQ / AWS IoT Core)
- JTAG programmer for Spartan-6

### FPGA Setup
```
1. Open project: fpga/relay_monitor.xise in Xilinx ISE
2. Run: Synthesize → Implement Design → Generate Programming File
3. Connect JTAG programmer to Spartan-6 board
4. Program via iMPACT or Vivado Hardware Manager
```

### NodeMCU Firmware
```
1. Install ESP8266 board package in Arduino IDE
2. Open: firmware/nodemcu_main.ino
3. Edit config.h — set Wi-Fi SSID, password, MQTT broker IP
4. Set baud rate to match FPGA UART receiver (e.g. 9600)
5. Upload to NodeMCU
```

